1 I grew up in Houston and was nine when this movie came out . As a result I do n't remember anything about the movie . But I do remember the sensation it caused from Gilley 's and the mechanical bull to Johnny Lee 's hit song " Lookin ' for Love " which still brings back memories of childhood whenever I hear it.<br /><br />However , a few years ago I saw this movie for the first time as an adult and all I can say is , I was blown away . Few movies have hit me harder . This movie is as raw and real as you can get . From Uncle Bob 's ranch house , the chemical plant in Texas City , Gilley 's dance hall , and Bud and Sissy . And maybe for that reason it does n't have a wider appeal . But no matter how you feel about country music ( I for one ca n't stand it despite my Houston roots ) Urban Cowboy is a unique slice of American pie . For that reason I love it !
